==English==

===Etymology===
From ''[[Bolshevik]]'', the socialist party in the 1918 Russian Revolution, from Russian ''Bolsheviki'', "majority faction"

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# (''derogatory, Britain, dated'') a government leftist, especially a [[communist]], [[socialist]], or labour union leader

===Adjective===
{{en-adj-er-e|bolshi}}
# difficult or rebellious
#:''Timothy, don't be so '''bolshie!'''''

